{"type":"message","id":"b219a7a9","parentId":"82341c8d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:17:47.795Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x77m44vvhxle_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5036\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2334\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] tic/tic_classifier.ps1\r\n[mutation proposed] tic/tic_classifier.ps1\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 081716 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs and tests if these invariants can predict subsequent pulse content.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"quiet-trail","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5036\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2334\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] tic/tic_classifier.ps1\r\n[mutation proposed] tic/tic_classifier.ps1\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 081716 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs and tests if these invariants can predict subsequent pulse content.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774354667793}}
{"type":"message","id":"20da6e9a","parentId":"b219a7a9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:17:47.797Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x77m44vvhxle_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 081616\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- Key insight identified: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- Next action defined: TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n- Pending: Implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe pending action is clear: Implement TIC classifier to test the hypothesis that causal discovery and compression are the same problem.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse log files to understand their structure\r\n2. Implement a TIC classifier that can identify invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Measure classification accuracy and next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLet me start by examining the pulse log structure to understand what I'm working with, then implement the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, I should first check if there are any pulse log files in the logs directory, then implement the TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\n\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is established but not yet validated empirically. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next concrete step to test whether causal structure discovery and compression are the same problem.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\n\r\nImplement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier experiment. I'll create a Python script that analyzes pulse logs to identify invariant vs variant content, then tests next-pulse prediction accuracy. This validates the core hypothesis that a compressor finding invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\r\nTests the hypothesis that causal structure = invariant structure\r\n\r\nHypothesis: A compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\nIf this holds, then:\r\n1. Invariant/variant classification should be >70% accurate\r\n2. Next-pulse prediction from invariants should be >60% accurate\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom typing import List, Tuple, Dict\r\n\r\n# Configuration\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_PULSES = 5  # Minimum pulses needed for analysis\r\nINVARIANCE_THRESHOLD = 0.6  # Appears in >=60% of pulses = invariant\r\n\r\nclass PulseAnalyzer:\r\n    def __init__(self, log_dir: Path):\r\n        self.log_dir = log_dir\r\n        self.pulses = []\r\n        self.content_segments = []\r\n        \r\n    def load_pulses(self) -> List[dict]:\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse log files chronologically.\"\"\"\r\n        pulse_files = sorted(self.log_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n        for pf in pulse_files:\r\n            with open(pf, 'r') as f:\r\n                content = f.read()\r\n                self.pulses.append({\r\n                    'file': pf.name,\r\n                    'content': content,\r\n                    'segments': self._extract_segments(content)\r\n                })\r\n        return self.pulses\r\n    \r\n    def _extract_segments(self, content: str) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract meaningful segments from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n        # Remove headers, focus on content lines\r\n        lines = [l.strip() for l in content.split('\\n') \r\n                 if l.strip() and not l.startswith('#') \r\n                 and not l.startswith('---')]\r\n        # Split into sentence-like segments\r\n        segments = []\r\n        for line in lines:\r\n            # Split on common delimiters\r\n            parts = re.split(r'[.;:]| - ', line)\r\n            segments.extend([p.strip() for p in parts if p.strip() and len(p.strip()) > 10])\r\n        return segments\r\n    \r\n    def find_invariants(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:\r\n        \"\"\"Identify invariant (persistent) vs variant (unique) content.\"\"\"\r\n        # Count segment occurrences across all pulses\r\n        segment_counts = Counter()\r\n        for pulse in self.pulses:\r\n            seen_in_pulse = set()\r\n            for seg in pulse['segments']:\r\n                if seg not in seen_in_pulse:\r\n                    segment_counts[seg] += 1\r\n                    seen_in_pulse.add(seg)\r\n        \r\n        # Classify: invariant if appears in >= threshold of pulses\r\n        threshold_count = int(len(self.pulses) * INVARIANCE_THRESHOLD)\r\n        invariants = [seg for seg, count in segment_counts.items() \r\n                      if count >= threshold_count]\r\n        variants = [seg for seg, count in segment_counts.items() \r\n                    if count < threshold_count]\r\n        \r\n        return invariants, variants\r\n    \r\n    def test_classification(self, invariants: List[str], variants: List[str]) -> float:\r\n        \"\"\"Test classification accuracy using leave-one-out on last 5 pulses.\"\"\"\r\n        test_pulses = self.pulses[-5:] if len(self.pulses) >= 5 else self.pulses\r\n        train_pulses = self.pulses[:-5] if len(self.pulses) >= 5 else []\r\n        \r\n        if len(train_pulses) < 3:\r\n            print(f\"  ⚠️  Insufficient training pulses ({len(train_pulses)}), using all pulses\")\r\n            train_pulses = self.pulses\r\n        \r\n        # Recalculate invariants from training set only\r\n        train_segment_counts = Counter()\r\n        for pulse in train_pulses:\r\n            seen = set()\r\n            for seg in pulse['segments']:\r\n                if seg not in seen:\r\n                    train_segment_counts[seg] += 1\r\n                    seen.add(seg)\r\n        \r\n        threshold = int(len(train_pulses) * INVARIANCE_THRESHOLD)\r\n        train_invariants = {seg for seg, count in train_segment_counts.items() \r\n                           if count >= threshold}\r\n        \r\n        # Test on held-out pulses\r\n        correct = 0\r\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:16:43\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774354667795}}
